    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1868-09-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1868-09-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="110"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d110">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Johnson</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 18.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                >Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1868-09-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 17, 1868.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I inclose a copy of an instruction of the 8th
                    instant to Mr. J. Ross Browne, United States minister at Peking, relative to a
                    contemplated revision of the tariff and revenue parts of our former treaty with
                    China.</p>
                <p>This paper is furnished you, as is indicated therein, with a view to its being
                    used, if necessary, in preserving and maintaining a good understanding with the
                    British government in regard to the important subjects to which it relates.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Reverdy Johnson,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c.,
                            &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
